Ex-Deputy Governor of Lagos State, Alhaji Rafiu Jafojo, has been reported dead at the age of 80-years old. A report by Nation Newspaper revealed that Jafojo, who served as deputy to Alhaji Lateef Jakande, died on Saturday, April 23, 2016 after a brief illness. Top dignitaries that have been spotted at his Lagos residence include his former boss, Lateef Jakande and deputy governor of Lagos state,  Alhaja Dr. Idiat Oluranti Adebule. There are reports that Jafojo’s remain will be buried on Sunday, April 24, 2016 at 2pm according to Islamic rites. Source